The paper deals with the integral representation of the logarithmic function and its applications in information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves computations and formulas, which suggests it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of the logarithmic function in entropy evaluations and capacity calculations indicates that it could also be classified under cs.SI (Systems and Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
